Add the GraphQL schema types and resolver for the `generateCodeFromTask` mutation. This is the cross-group blocker task — it modifies `schema.ts` (typeDefs).

**1. TypeDefs in `apps/api/src/graphql/schema.ts`:**
Add these types BEFORE the Query type:
```graphql
type GeneratedFile {
  path: String!
  content: String!
  language: String!
  description: String!
}

type CodeGeneration {
  files: [GeneratedFile!]!
  summary: String!
  estimatedTokensUsed: Int!
}
```

Add this mutation to the Mutation type (after `generateTaskInstructions`):
```graphql
generateCodeFromTask(taskId: ID!): CodeGeneration!
```

**2. Resolver in `apps/api/src/graphql/resolvers/ai.ts`:**
Add `generateCodeFromTask` to `aiMutations`:
```typescript
generateCodeFromTask: async (_parent: unknown, args: { taskId: string }, context: Context) => {
  const user = requireOrg(context);
  const apiKey = requireApiKey(context);
  const task = await context.prisma.task.findUnique({
    where: { taskId: args.taskId },
    include: { project: true },
  });
  if (!task || task.orgId !== user.orgId) {
    throw new NotFoundError('Task not found');
  }
  if (!task.instructions) {
    throw new ValidationError('Task has no instructions. Generate instructions first.');
  }
  return aiGenerateCode(
    apiKey,
    task.title,
    task.description ?? '',
    task.instructions,
    task.project.name,
    task.project.description ?? '',
  );
},
```

Import `generateCode as aiGenerateCode` from `../../ai/index.js` at the top of the file (add to existing import).

**Verification:** `pnpm --filter api typecheck` passes. The mutation is callable from GraphQL.

Add the frontend flow: 'Generate Code' button on TaskDetailPanel → preview generated files → 'Create PR' button that calls existing `createPullRequestFromTask`.

**1. New component: `apps/web/src/components/CodePreviewModal.tsx`:**
A modal/slide-over that shows generated code files with a 'Create PR' action.

Props:
```typescript
interface CodePreviewModalProps {
  isOpen: boolean;
  onClose: () => void;
  files: Array<{ path: string; content: string; language: string; description: string }>;
  summary: string;
  estimatedTokensUsed: number;
  onCreatePR: (files: Array<{ path: string; content: string }>) => Promise<void>;
  isCreatingPR: boolean;
}
```

UI layout:
- Modal overlay with max-w-4xl width
- Header: 'Generated Code' title + summary text + token cost display (show `estimatedTokensUsed` as 'Estimated tokens: X')
- File list: each file as a collapsible section:
  - Header: file path (monospace) + language badge + description
  - Body: `<pre><code>` block with the content (use `whitespace-pre-wrap` and `overflow-x-auto`)
  - Default: first file expanded, rest collapsed
- Footer: 'Cancel' button (closes modal) + 'Create Pull Request' button (calls `onCreatePR` with the files array mapped to `{path, content}` only)
- While creating PR: show spinner on the button, disable both buttons
- After PR created successfully: show success message with PR URL (or just close and let toast handle it)

Use Tailwind classes consistent with existing modals (see `SprintCreateModal` pattern).

**2. Mutations in `apps/web/src/hooks/useProjectData.ts`:**

Add new state variables:
```typescript
const [generatedCode, setGeneratedCode] = useState<{
  files: Array<{ path: string; content: string; language: string; description: string }>;
  summary: string;
  estimatedTokensUsed: number;
} | null>(null);
const [generatingCode, setGeneratingCode] = useState<string | null>(null); // taskId
const [creatingPR, setCreatingPR] = useState(false);
```

Add `handleGenerateCode` function:
```typescript
const handleGenerateCode = async (task: Task) => {
  const controller = new AbortController();
  abortRef.current = controller;
  setGeneratingCode(task.taskId);
  try {
    const data = await gql<{ generateCodeFromTask: { files: ..., summary: string, estimatedTokensUsed: number } }>(
      `mutation($taskId: ID!) { generateCodeFromTask(taskId: $taskId) { files { path content language description } summary estimatedTokensUsed } }`,
      { taskId: task.taskId },
      controller.signal
    );
    setGeneratedCode(data.generateCodeFromTask);
  } catch (err: unknown) {
    if ((err as Error).name !== 'AbortError') {
      showToast((err as Error).message || 'Code generation failed', 'error');
    }
  } finally {
    setGeneratingCode(null);
    if (abortRef.current === controller) abortRef.current = null;
  }
};
```

Add `handleCreatePR` function:
```typescript
const handleCreatePR = async (files: Array<{ path: string; content: string }>) => {
  if (!selectedTask || !projectId) return;
  setCreatingPR(true);
  try {
    await gql(
      `mutation($projectId: ID!, $taskId: ID!, $files: [GitHubFileInput!]!) { createPullRequestFromTask(projectId: $projectId, taskId: $taskId, files: $files) { url number } }`,
      { projectId, taskId: selectedTask.taskId, files }
    );
    showToast('Pull request created!', 'success');
    setGeneratedCode(null);
  } catch (err: unknown) {
    showToast((err as Error).message || 'Failed to create PR', 'error');
  } finally {
    setCreatingPR(false);
  }
};
```

Export new values from the hook: `generatedCode, setGeneratedCode, generatingCode, creatingPR, handleGenerateCode, handleCreatePR`.
Add to the `ProjectDataReturn` interface.

**3. Wire into `apps/web/src/pages/ProjectDetail.tsx`:**
- Import `CodePreviewModal` component
- Pass `handleGenerateCode` as `onGenerateCode` prop to `TaskDetailContent`
- Pass `generatingCode` to TaskDetailPanel
- Render `CodePreviewModal` when `generatedCode` is not null
- Pass `handleCreatePR` as `onCreatePR` to the modal
- Pass `d.projectHasRepo` — if project has no repo, show a message in the modal that a repo will be auto-created

**4. Update `apps/web/src/components/TaskDetailPanel.tsx`:**
Add a 'Generate Code' button next to the existing 'Generate Instructions' button.
- Only show when task has `instructions` (code gen requires instructions)
- Button text: `generatingCode === task.taskId ? 'Generating code…' : '⌨ Generate code'`
- Calls `onGenerateCode(task)` on click
- Disabled when `disabled || generatingCode === task.taskId`
- Add `onGenerateCode` to the props interface and destructure it
- Add `generatingCode` prop (string | null)

